This paper is about developing dialogue agents that can recognize and respond to emotions in a conversation partner, which is a key challenge in natural language processing and human-computer interaction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and understanding. The paper also proposes a new dataset and benchmark for empathetic dialogue generation, which involves training and evaluating machine learning models, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of empathetic communication in human-computer interaction, which falls under the scope of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
